U of T Language Exchange Initiative (LEI) Language Teachers/Executives Recruitment 

In the long flow of human history, language has stood as one of the most representative aspects of our culture. With their countless styles and forms, words capture and record our lives. Through our knowledge of language, we can savor the stories of everyone around (and even beyond?) the globe. 

If you are interested in teaching a language, feel free to sign up! (Link in bio.)
We are still accepting applications and are especially in need of Japanese, Korean, and Spanish teachers. 

Yi-Lun Huang 
President, LEI

Exciting news! 🎉 

On September 16th, 2024, 
from 5-7pm at OISE2214, 

We’re teaming up with students from the Fukuoka Institute of Technology for a fun and interactive English practice session🇨🇦🇯🇵

Don’t miss this chance to connect with Japanese students, share cultures, and help them improve their English skills🗣️🌟

Space is limited to 20 attendees, so sign up early to secure your spot! ‼️‼️‼️

You can sign up with the following link or in our bio/stories! 

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSe3n7Sfs3nJm_lC9Um_Qr6H0bipdoOCmrnFT7HGcgy5NnDggQ/viewform
